text_answer.content: I'm not sure I agree with the Drawing Conclusions question. The text doesn't give strong evidence that Max's grandfather knew he would travel in time, only that his grandfather knew that's what Max did when he left the room. Max meets his grandfather in 1985, and his grandfather says the temporal displacement device wasn't ready for testing. This means that in 1985, Max's grandfather was working on time travel, so he was definitely working on it for decades as Choice A suggests.
